On Thu, 17 Nov 2005, C. Dreike, Advantage Automation, Inc wrote:

> Hi,
>
> What is the droaning moaning noise heard when driving at 65-70 (3500-4000+
> rpm)? Is there a resonance in the engine? I have had this noise on 3 engines
> so far. The current one has a counterbalanced crank.
> Anyone know?

It's a rumble of discontent amongst the squirrels.  You're working them
too hard.

> I know that Bernie Bergman sells a steel pulley and claims it damps out
> something.

It _might_ damp out torsional vibrations in the crank.  OTOH,
it might actually increase it, depending upon the crank, flywheel, and
pulley combination.  I wouldn't go there unless you have the capability of
doing torsional testing on the whole assembly.

George
